people don't even know where they are.

30
00:04:23,563 --> 00:04:25,053
They're not gonna hurt you.

31
00:04:25,131 --> 00:04:28,294
In a few minutes, we're gonna be in a room
with a killer. That doesn't bother you?

32
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:30,996
Hey, you're the one that
wanted to major in journalism.

33
00:04:36,409 --> 00:04:38,570
These are the people
from that newspaper deal.

34
00:04:38,645 --> 00:04:41,136
- Oh, yeah. From the college?
- Yes, sir.

35
00:04:41,214 --> 00:04:43,205
- I'm Jerry Woolridge.
- Nice to meet you.

36
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:45,649
I'm Marsha Dwiggins and
this is Theresa Evans.

37
00:04:45,718 --> 00:04:48,448
She's here to take the pictures.

38
00:04:48,521 --> 00:04:50,853
Y'all sit down.

39
00:04:51,891 --> 00:04:54,121
Yeah, there was a young
man named John Legit Hunter

40
00:04:54,193 --> 00:04:56,957
who was in the filling station business
- a good filling station business.

41
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:59,362
But he was one of these young
men we run across in life,

42
00:04:59,432 --> 00:05:02,833
I'm sure you've run across 'em, who
didn't deserve what he had, you know?

43
00:05:02,902 --> 00:05:07,202
And one of the things he had was this...

44
00:05:07,273 --> 00:05:09,264
beautiful young bride,

45
00:05:09,342 --> 00:05:12,106
Sarah.

46
00:05:12,178 --> 00:05:14,078
She was a Georgia peach.

47
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:19,949
In fact, she was more like the picture I
had in my mind than any woman I'd ever seen.

48
00:05:20,019 --> 00:05:23,477
So I took it upon myself to take
her away from John Legit Hunter,

49
00:05:23,556 --> 00:05:26,457
who did not deserve her, you know?

50
00:05:26,526 --> 00:05:29,620
Oh, I don't know if I told you,

51
00:05:29,696 --> 00:05:34,258
but he was a Frenchman who
claimed to be an Englishman.

52
00:05:36,602 --> 00:05:39,662
Yeah... Took a lot of strong nylon
cord to get her away from him,

53
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:44,472
'cause she was a fighter as
well as being a Georgia peach.

54
00:05:46,946 --> 00:05:50,939
I think there must have
been a little mix-up.

55
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,986
I talked to your sponsor or
teacher, or whoever he is,

56
00:05:54,053 --> 00:05:57,489
and I told him that there
couldn't be any pictures.

57
00:05:57,557 --> 00:06:02,961
It's supposed to be like an article or a
story, something like that, isn't that right?

58
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:06,362
Well, yeah, it's for the school
newspaper, but it has pictures.

59
00:06:06,432 --> 00:06:08,764
I mean, it's a regular paper, you know?

60
00:06:08,835 --> 00:06:11,360
Karl's real sensitive about
having his picture made.

61
00:06:11,437 --> 00:06:14,873
He wouldn't even be on the bulletin
board for the Easter collage.

62
00:06:18,077 --> 00:06:20,841
Now...

63
00:06:20,913 --> 00:06:24,508
a shovel just makes
too goddamn much racket.

64
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:36,856
All I can do is talk to
him, see what he says.

65
00:06:38,431 --> 00:06:40,922
You gotta make something
explode to truly understand it.

66
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:46,996
I mean, you gotta examine all those little
tiny particles while they're still on fire.

67
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:50,065
("Guard) Karl, I've gotta take
you down to the old classroom.

68
00:06:50,143 --> 00:06:55,046
Mr. Woolridge has some people
for you to see down there.

69
00:06:55,114 --> 00:06:57,275
Come on, let's go.

70
00:07:15,468 --> 00:07:18,995
You remember me telling you about
those people from that newspaper?

71
00:07:19,071 --> 00:07:22,199
They wanna ask you some
questions about your release.

72
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:25,108
They think it'll make a good story.

73
00:07:25,178 --> 00:07:28,375
